section.section:
The minimum standards of valuation for certificates issued on or after January 1, 1998, shall be based on the following tables:
for certificates of life insurance:
the Commissioners 1941 Standard Ordinary Mortality Table;
the Commissioners 1941 Standard Industrial Mortality Table;
the Commissioners 1958 Standard Ordinary Mortality Table;
the Commissioners 1980 Standard Ordinary Mortality Table; or
any more recent table authorized for use under § 5-304(b) of this article; and
for annuity and pure endowment certificates, total and permanent disability benefits, accidental death benefits, and noncancelable accident and health benefits, the tables that are authorized for use by life insurers in the State.
